    • clickAddProductSaveButton

      public void clickAddProductSaveButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      Depending on the data entered by the user, either the product is added upon the user selecting the "save" button (in which they are returned to the Main Screen), or various error messages will pop up, depending on what data is missing or invalid.
      Parameters:
      event - user selects the "save" button.
      Throws:
      IOException - from FXMLLoader.

    • clickAssociatedPartAddButton

      public void clickAssociatedPartAddButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Add part to product (associated part table).
      Parameters:
      event - user selects the add button to add associated part to product. 1. User first picks a part to add. 2. User then presses the Add button. 3. The part that the user picked is then added to the product's associated part table. Note: If user presses the Remove Associated Part button before picking a part first, a pop-up error message will display.

    • clickAssociatedPartRemoveButton

      public void clickAssociatedPartRemoveButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Remove part from product (associated part table).
      Parameters:
      event - user selects the remove button to remove associated part from product. 1. User first picks an associated part to remove. 2. User then presses the Remove Associated Part button. 3. The part that the user picked is then removed from the product's associated part table. Note: If user presses the Remove Associated Part button before picking a part first, a pop-up error message will display.

    • searchBy_PartName_or_ID

      public void searchBy_PartName_or_ID(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Search Part by ID or partial or full name.
      Parameters:
      event - user presses the enter key on their keyboard to perform part search. 1. User types partial or full Part name, or Part ID, of the part they wish to search for in the "Search by Part ID or Name" text field. 2. User presses the enter key on their keyboard. 3. If a match or multiple matches are found, then the matching search results are displayed. Note: If no matching search results are found, then a warning message box will display stating that there were no matching results found.
